1: While you are [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, your body rots over the course of four days, after which the rotting stops. You lose your hair by the end of day 1, finger tips and toe tips by the end of day 2, lips and nose by the end of day 3, and ears by the end of day 4. A [[regeneration]] spell restores lost body parts.
2: When you first [[attune|attunement]] to the artifact, it gives you a quest determined by the GM. You must complete this quest as if affected by the [[geas]] spell. Once you complete the quest, you are no longer affected by this property.
3: The artifact houses a bodiless life force that is hostile toward you. Each time you use one of the artifact's properties and suffer a [[consequence]], there is a chance that the life force tries to leave the artifact and enter your body. If you fail to resist, you become an NPC under the GM's control until the intruding life force is banished using magic such as the [[dispel immortal]] spell.
4: Creatures with a [[creature tier]] of 0, as well as plants that aren't creatures, wither and die when within 10 feet of the artifact.
5: The artifact imprisons a [[creature tier]] 3 [[immortal]]. Each time you use one of the artifact's properties, the immortal has a small chance of escaping, whereupon it appears within 15 feet of you and attacks you.
6: While you are [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, creatures of a particular type other than [[humanoid]] (as chosen by the GM) are always hostile toward you.
7: The artifact dilutes magic potions within 10 feet of it, rendering them nonmagical.
8: The artifact erases magic scrolls with in 10 feet of it, rendering them nonmagical.
9: Before using one of the artifact's properties, you must first draw blood, either from yourself or from a willing or incapacitated creature within your reach.
10: When you become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you gain a form of [[long-term madness]].
11: You suffer 3 [[harm]] as psychic damage when you become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact.
12: Before you can become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you must kill a nonhostile or allied living creature.
13: When you become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, one of your [[approach]]es is reduced by 1 at random. A rare-tier [[restoration]] spell restores the ability to normal.
14: Each time you become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you age <<dr "3d10">> years. If you die from this, you are instantly transformed into a [[wight]] under the GM's control that is sworn to protect the artifact.
15: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you lose the ability to speak.
16: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, each time you suffer [[harm]], suffer 1 additional harm.
17: When you become [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you attract the attention of a powerful [[immortal]] that eventually sends a [[creature tier]] 4 avatar to wrest the artifact from you. Once it obtains the artifact, the avatar vanishes.
18: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you have [[disadvantage]] when resisting the effects of spells.
19: The first time you touch a gem or piece of jewelry while [[attuned|attunement]] to this artifact, the value of the gem or jewelry is reduced by half.
20: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you are blinded when you are more than 10 feet away from it.
21: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you are extremely vulnerable to poison.
22: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you emit a sour stench noticeable from up to 10 feet away.
23: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, all [[holy water]] within 10 feet of you is destroyed.
24: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you are physically ill and have [[disadvantage]] on any attempt made difficult by nausea.
25: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, your weight increases by <<dr "1d4">> × 10 pounds.
26: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, your appearance changes as the GM decides.
27: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you are deafened when you are more than 10 feet away from it.
28: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, your weight drops by <<dr "1d4">> × 5 pounds.
29: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can't smell.
30: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, nonmagical flames are extinguished within 30 feet of you.
31: While you are [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, other creatures can't sleep or have restorative rest while within 300 feet of you.
32: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, any plant you touch that isn't a [[creature|plant creature]] rapidly withers and rots.
33: While you are [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, animals within 30 feet of you are hostile toward you.
34: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you must eat and drink six times the normal amount each day.
35: While you are [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, your flaw [[aspect]] is amplified in a way determined by the GM.